<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,1581,2024]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats., 2006 (C.Presl)" authorityName="Ebihara &amp; K.Iwats., 2006 (C.Presl)" box="[315,474,1582,1607]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Microgonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,474,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Microgonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by four species. All Comorian species have glabrous lamina margins, submarginal false veins and sori more or less immerged in the laminae with tubular base and lips more or less developed, sometimes dilated as a collar but never bilabiate, and with undifferentiated margins. The widespread 
<taxonomicName box="[501,675,1686,1712]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[501,675,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was cited for the archipelago in literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[1206,1342,1686,1712]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux 2009</bibRefCitation>
) but represented in collection by only four specimens. This contradicts its supposed abundance in the region, as well observed in Mascarenes (pers. obs.; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grangaud E." box="[803,991,1755,1781]" journalOrPublisher="MNHN, Paris &amp; Biotope, Meze" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Grangaud E. 2010. Guide des Fougeres et plantes alliees des Mascareignes. MNHN, Paris &amp; Biotope, Meze." title="Guide des Fougeres et plantes alliees des Mascareignes" type="book" year="2010">Grangaud 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In addition the species is usually distributed from sea level up to 1350–1400 m, and more frequently below 1000 m. All the supposedly Comorian specimens (including recent collects firstly identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1173,1825,1851]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[999,1173,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were collected at high elevations, above 1000 m. A precise investigation of these specimens reveals in fact that they are not 
<taxonomicName box="[238,413,1894,1920]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[238,413,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but rather the distinct 
<taxonomicName authority="(Willd.) J. P. Roux." authorityName="(Willd.) J.P.Roux." box="[700,1051,1894,1921]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[700,825,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. erosum</emphasis>
(Willd.) J.P.Roux.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1398,1894,1920]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[1063,1398,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Didymoglossum cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be absent in Comoros but confusion with 
<taxonomicName box="[781,905,1930,1955]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[781,905,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as detailed here-after remains easy. This explains why we, however, chose to maintain 
<taxonomicName box="[732,903,1964,1990]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[732,903,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Xper database, in order to allow its potential identification in future collects.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
